  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria (major):

          1. Between 18 and 75 years of age, inclusive.

          2. Have an indication for the use of clopidogrel defined as either spontaneous MI
             [hospitalized with final diagnosis of MI, excluding periprocedural or definite
             secondary MI (e.g., due to anemia or hypertensive emergency)] or PCI within the past 6
             months.

          3. Clinically stable and at least 4 weeks following the MI or PCI.

        Exclusion Criteria (major):

          1. Conditions that alter platelet function.

          2. Conditions that increase bleeding risk.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
